race.comment: TAKE A BOW (7) is racing better than her form reads and has a solid record at this track. At peak fitness now and capable of breaking through. HOME ZONE (8) last appeared 11 weeks ago when she finished 2.75 lengths from the winner in fourth over 1212m at Geelong. Managed to fill a minor placing first-up last prep at Swan Hill over 1200m. In the mix. MISHANI CROWN (2) has good early speed and could take running down. KING OF THE JUNGLE (3) is usually thereabouts and worth including in any wider plays, as is A TOUCH FROM FAYT (6) who has been in the market at her last couple of starts but hasn't made an impression, last start running fifth at this track. Has upside and gets chance.
